com.projetloki.genesis.image

Class Point

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.projetloki.genesis.image.Point
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class Point
extends Object
implements Serializable
    An immutable point, located by its x- and y- coordinates in the plane. In the field of computer graphics, points with a low y-coordinate are higher on the screen than points with a greater y-coordinate.

      • rotate

        public Point rotate(double theta,
           Point center)
        Returns the image of this point by the clockwise rotation through the angle theta around the point center.

        If you plan to rotate a great number of points through the same angle, it is faster to construct a rotation matrix for this angle and call rotate(RotationMatrix, Point) instead.

        Parameters:
        theta - in radians
        center - the rotation center
        Returns:
        the image of this by the specified rotation
